list.abstract: 空前绝后，汉语成语，意思是从前没有过，今后也不再有，形容十分难得，独一无二。例句为“ 万里长城的建造是空前绝后的”。该词出自宋代赵佶的《宣和画谱》：“顾（顾恺之，晋代画家）冠于前，张（张僧繇，南朝梁代画家）绝于后，而道子（吴道子，唐代画家）乃兼有之。” 近义词有前所未有，反义词有比比皆是。

yingyinNormal.en: This level of criminality is unprecedented, even on fucking Wall Street.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这种程度的犯罪就算是在华尔街也是前所未有的。

yingyinNormal.en: You stated that it was a dual engine failure due to multiple bird strikes? That would be unprecedented.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你说因遭飞鸟多次撞击造成双发停车？这是前所未有的情况。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, everything is unprecedented until it happens for the first time.
Then in the 1940s, the city abandoned streetcars and began an unprecedented freeway-building frenzy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在40年代时，城市遗弃了电车，开始空前的高速公路建造之旅。

yingyinNormal.en: Amidst unprecedented scenes, there was uproar in court as Sherlock Holmes was vindicated and cleared of all suspicion.
yingyinNormal.zh: 事态急转直下，法庭群情激奋，夏洛克被判无罪 洗脱所有嫌疑。

yingyinNormal.en: Focus up. I'm sorry, did I just mishear you or did you agree with me. Oh, I want to take it back. No. You can't retract it. Thank you. Unprecedented.
yingyinNormal.zh: 慢着。抱歉，是我听错了吗？你是在支持我吗？我想反悔了。不不，不能收回。谢谢啊，真是破天荒。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, so just the four of us. Before we begin, this may have some unprecedented tax implications. In fact, we should start early cause we are gonna be on the phone with the IRS for hours.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧那就我们四个人挖。在我们开挖前先说好这可能会造成史无前例的税务问题。其实我们最好快点开始到时候国税局可能会打电话跟我们谈很久呢。

yingyinNormal.en: You see, this trench is as important to manufacturing today as the railroads were in 19th-century America, because it holds something that is connecting every home in this remote area to the world, something that's distributing goods and ideas on an unprecedented scale, fiber-optic cable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个海沟对于现在的制造业很重要，十九世纪美国的铁路因为它，拥有一些世界上远程连接每家每户的东西，一些分发物品，分享信息规模之大史无前例。光纤电缆。
